data.Name: Silver
data.Description: Silver is a highly conductive and malleable precious metal, commonly used in jewelry, electronics, and coins.

data.Name: Sulphur
data.Description: Sulphur is a yellow, nonmetallic element used primarily in the production of fertilizers and industrial chemicals.

data.Name: Vanadium
data.Description: Vanadium is a hard, silvery-grey metal used to produce strong steel alloys and in some chemical reactions.

data.Name: Arsenic
data.Description: Arsenic is a toxic metalloid used in various industrial processes and historically as a pesticide.

data.Name: Chlorine
data.Description: Chlorine is a highly reactive, greenish-yellow gas used for water purification and in the production of numerous everyday products.

data.Name: Chromium
data.Description: Chromium is a lustrous, hard metal known for its high corrosion resistance and use in stainless steel.

data.Name: Strontium
data.Description: Strontium is a soft, silvery metal used in fireworks and in the medical field for bone imaging agents.

data.Name: Barium
data.Description: Barium is a soft, silvery alkaline earth metal, used primarily in drilling fluids and in making various barium compounds.

data.Name: Cobalt
data.Description: Cobalt is a hard, lustrous grey metal used in batteries, magnets, and high-strength alloys.

data.Name: Bismuth
data.Description: Bismuth is a brittle, crystalline, white metal used in low-melting alloys and pharmaceuticals.

data.Name: Rubidium
data.Description: Rubidium is a soft, silvery-white metallic element used in photoelectric cells and as a getter in vacuum tubes.

data.Name: Bromine
data.Description: Bromine is a deep-red, corrosive liquid used in flame retardants and in the manufacture of various chemicals.

data.Name: Zircon
data.Description: Zircon is a mineral used primarily in ceramic glazes and as an abrasive.

data.Name: Cadmium
data.Description: Cadmium is a toxic, bluish-white metal used in batteries and for corrosion protection coatings.

data.Name: Nickel
data.Description: Nickel is a hard, ductile metal used in stainless steel, batteries, and as a catalyst.

data.Name: Yttrium
data.Description: Yttrium is a silver-metallic element used in electronics, superconductors, and as an additive in alloys.

data.Name: Cerium
data.Description: Cerium is a soft, silvery metal used in catalytic converters and as a polishing agent.

data.Name: Copper
data.Description: Copper is a highly conductive metal used extensively in electrical wiring and plumbing.

data.Name: Niobium
data.Description: Niobium is a soft, grey metal used in superalloys for jet engines and in superconducting magnets.

data.Name: Hafnium
data.Description: Hafnium is a shiny, silvery metal used in nuclear reactors' control rods and in high-temperature alloys.

data.Name: Zinc
data.Description: Zinc is a corrosion-resistant metal used in galvanizing, alloys, and batteries.

data.Name: Gallium
data.Description: Gallium is a soft, silvery metal used in semiconductors and LEDs.

data.Name: Thorium
data.Description: Thorium is a radioactive metallic element used as a nuclear fuel and in magnesium alloys.

data.Name: Germanium
data.Description: Germanium is a hard, grayish-white metalloid used in semiconductors and fiber optics.

data.Name: Uranium
data.Description: Uranium is a dense, radioactive metal used primarily as fuel in nuclear power plants.

data.Name: Cesium
data.Description: Cesium is a soft, gold-colored, highly reactive metal used in atomic clocks and photoelectric cells.

data.Name: Selenium
data.Description: Selenium is a nonmetal used in photocells, pigments, and as an additive to glass and animal feeds.

data.Name: Mercury
data.Description: Mercury is a liquid metal at room temperature, historically used in thermometers and electrical switches.

data.Name: Iodine
data.Description: Iodine is a dark, purple-black crystalline solid used in disinfectants and nutritional supplements.

data.Name: Molybdenum
data.Description: Molybdenum is a silvery metal used to strengthen steel and as a catalyst in the petroleum industry.

data.Name: Indium
data.Description: Indium is a soft, malleable metal used in LCD screens and solders.

data.Name: Lanthanum
data.Description: Lanthanum is a soft, malleable, silvery-white metal used in camera lenses and as a catalyst in refining.

data.Name: Lead
data.Description: Lead is a dense, soft, low-melting metal used in batteries and shields against radiation.

data.Name: Scandium
data.Description: Scandium is a soft, silvery metal used in aerospace components and in sports equipment like baseball bats.

data.Name: Tin
data.Description: Tin is a soft, malleable metal used in soldering, plating, and making bronze.

data.Name: Antimony
data.Description: Antimony is a brittle metalloid used in flame retardants, alloys, and semiconductors.

data.Name: Tellurium
data.Description: Tellurium is a brittle, mildly toxic metalloid used in solar panels and as an additive to steel and copper.

data.Name: Tantalum
data.Description: Tantalum is a hard, blue-gray metal highly resistant to corrosion and used in electronic components.

data.Name: Tungston
data.Description: Tungsten is a hard, dense metal with the highest melting point, used in light bulb filaments and cutting tools.

data.Name: Thallium
data.Description: Thallium is a soft, malleable, highly toxic metal used in electronic devices and as a rat poison.

data.Name: Aluminium
data.Description: Aluminium is a lightweight, silvery-white metal used widely in transportation, packaging, and construction.

data.Name: Gold
data.Description: Gold is a dense, soft, shiny metal highly valued for use in jewelry, electronics, and as monetary reserves.

data.Name: Calcium
data.Description: Calcium is an alkaline earth metal essential for biological organisms, used in cement and for reducing metals.

data.Name: Iron
data.Description: Iron is a common, hard metal used as the primary constituent in steel and various other alloys.

data.Name: Potassium
data.Description: Potassium is a soft, silvery-white metal that reacts violently with water, used in fertilizers and as a salt substitute.

data.Name: Magnesium
data.Description: Magnesium is a light, silvery-white metal used in alloys, fireworks, and in medical applications.

data.Name: Manganese
data.Description: Manganese is a hard metal used in steel production and batteries.

data.Name: Palladium
data.Description: Palladium is a rare, lustrous metal used in catalytic converters, electronics, and jewelry.

data.Name: Phosphorus
data.Description: Phosphorus is a reactive, nonmetallic element used in fertilizers, detergents, and incendiaries.

data.Name: Silica
data.Description: Silica is a hard, crystalline compound used in glass making, ceramics, and as a building material.

data.Name: Titanium
data.Description: Titanium is a strong, lightweight metal used in aerospace, medical devices, and pigments.

data.Name: Neodymium
data.Description: Neodymium is a soft, silvery metal used in powerful magnets and lasers.

data.Name: Praseodymium
data.Description: Praseodymium is a soft, silvery, malleable metal used in magnets, lasers, and in alloys for aircraft engines.

data.Name: Berylium
data.Description: Beryllium is a rare, lightweight, brittle metal used in aerospace materials and nuclear reactors.

data.Name: Samarium
data.Description: Samarium is a moderately hard silvery metal that is stable in dry air used in magnets and nuclear reactors.

data.Name: Europium
data.Description: Europium is a moderately hard, silvery metal that reacts quickly with water and air, used in nuclear reactors and as a red phosphor in TVs.

data.Name: Gadolinium
data.Description: Gadolinium is a silvery-white, malleable, and ductile rare earth metal used in MRI contrast agents and in alloys.

data.Name: Terbium
data.Description: Terbium is a silvery-white rare earth metal used in solid-state devices and as a doping agent in calcium fluoride.

data.Name: Dysprosium
data.Description: Dysprosium is a rare earth element with a high magnetic strength used in magnets and lasers.

data.Name: Holmium
data.Description: Holmium is a rare earth metal used in lasers and as a neutron absorber in nuclear reactors.

data.Name: Erbium
data.Description: Erbium is a silvery-white solid metal when artificially isolated, natural erbium is always found in chemical combination with other elements used in photographic filters and lasers.

data.Name: Thulium
data.Description: Thulium is the least abundant of the naturally occurring lanthanides used in portable X-ray devices.

data.Name: Ytterbium
data.Description: Ytterbium is a soft, malleable, and ductile chemical element that brightens in air and is used in certain alloys.

data.Name: Lutetium
data.Description: Lutetium is a silvery-white metal, which is the last element in the lanthanide series, used in PET scans and high-refractive index glass.

data.Name: Lithium
data.Description: Lithium is a soft, silvery-white metal used in batteries, mood-stabilizing drugs, and heat-resistant glass and ceramics.

data.Name: Helium
data.Description: Helium is a colorless, odorless, tasteless inert gas used in balloons, as a cooling medium in nuclear reactors, and in cryogenic research.

data.Name: Neon
data.Description: Neon is a noble gas used in neon advertising signs and high-voltage indicators, and as a cryogenic refrigerant.

data.Name: Argon
data.Description: Argon is an inert gas used in light bulbs, double-pane windows, and arc welding.

data.Name: Krypton
data.Description: Krypton is a noble gas used in lighting products and in scientific research.

data.Name: Ruthenium
data.Description: Ruthenium is a rare transition metal belonging to the platinum group, used in wear-resistant electrical contacts and thick-film resistors.

data.Name: Rhodium
data.Description: Rhodium is a rare, silvery-white, hard, and chemically inert transition metal used as a catalyst in the automotive industry and in jewelry plating.

data.Name: Xenon
data.Description: Xenon is a colorless, dense, odorless noble gas used in light emission applications and as an anesthetic.

data.Name: Rhenium
data.Description: Rhenium is a silvery-white metal or a grey powder used in high-temperature turbine engines and in thermocouples.

data.Name: Osmium
data.Description: Osmium is a hard, brittle, bluish-white transition metal used in alloys with platinum and for pen tips and compass bearings.

data.Name: Iridium
data.Description: Iridium is a very hard, brittle, silvery-white transition metal of the platinum group, used in high-temperature and corrosive environments.

data.Name: Platinum
data.Description: Platinum is a dense, malleable, ductile, highly unreactive, precious, silver-white transition metal used in jewelry, catalytic converters, and equipment used in chemical reactions.

data.Name: Protactinium
data.Description: Protactinium is a dense, silvery-gray metal used in the study of the nuclear reactions and found in the decay chain of uranium-235.

data.Name: Boron
data.Description: Boron is a metalloid essential for plant growth and used in borosilicate glass and as a semiconductor.

data.Name: Carbon
data.Description: Carbon is a versatile element that forms the basis of all known life and is used in a vast array of industrial processes.

data.Name: Fluorine
data.Description: Fluorine is a highly reactive, pale yellow gas used in toothpaste and refrigerants.

data.Name: Hydrogen
data.Description: Hydrogen is the lightest and most abundant chemical element, used in fuel cells and as a rocket fuel.

data.Name: Nitrogen
data.Description: Nitrogen is a colorless, odorless gas used as a fertilizer in agriculture and as a preservative in food packaging.

data.Name: Sodium
data.Description: Sodium is a soft, silvery-white, highly reactive metal used in table salt and various industrial processes.

data.Name: Promethium
data.Description: Promethium is a rare earth metal that emits beta radiation and is used in luminous paint and nuclear batteries.
